profile_positions.description:
The School Development Adviser role includes:
- strategic development of curriculum, pedagogy and policy;
- recruitment induction and performance management of principals and advisers;
- quality assurance through data analysis, school visits and reviews;
- strategic and budget management of professional development; and
- environmental and sustainability education strategy.

I currently co-lead the team of education advisers at ESF Centre with my colleague David Fitzgerald. I manage other colleagues who have responsibility for: developing professional development; secondary school curriculum and pedagogy; Chinese curriculum and pedagogy;and student attainment data. We also run networks of development groups which bring together expertise from the schools to provide expertise.

volunteer_experiences.description:
For 10 years, I took on various roles to support this development education NGO based in Birmingham, England. http://www.tidec.org/ These included:
- professional development in development education and global citizenship;
- editorial of publications - such as 'It is our world too' and 'Whose Citizenship?' etc;
- advising on work with schools and teachers in the UK;
I became a trustee on the board in 1999 and served until 2004.

For 10 years, I took on various roles to support this environmental education NGO.  These included:
- professional development on inquiry based learning in tropical environments;
- editorial of publications - such as Rainforest Resource Pack etc;
- advising on work with schools and teachers in the UK;
I became a trustee on the board in 1994 and served until 2000.
